SYMPTOM_TEXT: Headache began early afternoon and gradually the pain increased through the remainder of Friday March 5,2021 and lasted through Saturday, March 6,2021 until about 6 PM where the pain subsided enough that I could function. As the pain intensified, I had throbbing pain in the temples and behind my eyes, the pain worsened even more if I bent forward, like to pick up something from the floor. My neck muscles were extremely tight. I couldn't concentrate on anything, like reading or working.  I was feeling less than energetic,. Also, my left arm was red, not swollen at the injection site and hurt to touch, not as bad as the 2 days after receiving the vaccine, but I thought it was unusual that my arm was red & sore. This is what made me conclude it was a delayed reaction to the vaccine. I rarely have headaches and if I do  taking 2 Ibuprofen will take care of it. Taking 2 Ibuprofen this time did absolutely nothing to ease the pain.  I did increase to 800 mg of Ibuprofen late Friday and early Saturday which did help, used a cervical heating pad, hot shower to try to ease muscle tension. I was able to sleep and by Saturday evening with home remedies, the pain did subside and by Sunday March 7,2021 I felt back to normal with a slight, slight bit of headache but not much to worry about.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: IMMUNIZATION CLINIC NOTES:  77 y.o. female presented to Elementary School for second dose of COVID-19 vaccine. No known allergies. Patient reports history of hypertension, being treated with amlodipine. No history of asthma, COPD, use of inhaler for any conditions, or recent respiratory illness. Patient is a non-smoker. First dose of vaccine, Lot # 039K20A, administered on 2/6/2021 and patient reported no immediate symptoms during observation period after first dose. Second dose of vaccine, Lot# 013A21A, was administered on 3/5/2021 at 10:52AM to the left deltoid. Approximately 5 minutes after receiving second dose, patient reported feeling anxious and feeling like her blood pressure was increasing. Patient taken to EMS observation area. Patient observed by EMS.  Nurse assessed patient at 11:23AM. Patient was alert and oriented x 4. Manual blood pressure was 196/86. Pulse, manually palpated, was 86 and strong. SpO2 99% on room air.  Patient with flushing. No generalized hives. No itching. No swelling of face, lips, or eyes. Left deltoid injection site without erythema or swelling. Skin warm and dry. Lungs auscultated and inspiratory wheeze noted in all lung fields. No shortness of breath. No cough. No nasal congestion. No change in voice. No sensation of throat closing. No stridor.  No dizziness or syncope.  No GI symptoms.   Patient experiencing skin and respiratory symptoms. RN was asked to assess patient?s respiratory symptoms and also noted bilateral wheeze.  Patient?s symptoms post-vaccination involved more than one body system, skin and respiratory. Reviewed symptoms and standing order procedures with patient. Standing order for Medical Management of Vaccine Reactions in Adults in a Community Setting was followed. Patient was assisted to stretcher by EMS. 0.3mg epinephrine auto injector, Lot # G191202X Exp. 4/2021, was administered to the right outer thigh on 3/5/2021 at 11:39AM by RN. Patient was then transported by EMS to Medical Center.   EMERGENCY DEPARTMENT COURSE AND TREATMENT NOTE: Patient's condition remained stable during Emergency Department evaluation. Decision made to obtain prior medical records. (+)Prior records reviewed. There is low suspicion for an allergic reaction given symptoms. Patient is well appearing with a normal exam. Plan to monitor.  03/05/2021 13:13 Patient remains well appearing will discharge home.
HISTORY: Hypertension Thyroid cancer s/p thyroidectomy (not reported to staff at vaccination clinic, but reported during ED visit)

No rxn to dose 1. Dose 2: @10 min had tingling of lips; at 12 min had tingling of tongue [and anxiety from the tingling]; @ 15 min had some SOB and knew this was not just anxiety. Had zero intention of being taken to ER as I could easily tx myself. Took inhalers, extra cetirizine.  Did not take epi, though have several pens.  @4 hour started feeling weak, severe arm pain.  At 6 hours, unbearable arm pain, extreme weakness [did not take BP or pulse ox--though I can and wish I had]. Exceeding thirst, could not get water down fast enough. Reactivation of arachnoiditis symptoms. Started unusual muscle fasciculations in arms, leg, and face [face not normal for me]-took valium and baclofen. Next 36 hours  unable  Additional information for Item 18:  next 48 hours, unable to get out of bed other than to get water. Severe HA upon waking  [@16 H post injection].  Severe myalgias, but in areas of known arachnoiditis that have been quiescent for quite some time.  Forgot to mention, as I find this strange: prior to going to sleep I had left eye conjunctivitis.  Left eye only that still is slightly persistent and doesn't require any care [for me at least]  I am currently 72 hours post. Still with HA and some fatigue, though worked today [I WAH for a population health company].   L arm is not as painful as the excruciating pain @ hour  4-16, and no need for additional acetaminophen. I have an exceedingly high pain tolerance due to the arachnoiditis,  but this was the first time I took a narcotic in 5 years. 2 .5 mg oxycodone x1, then 600 mg ibuprofen x1, then 1 gm acetaminophen  2 over next 24 hours and nothing since, but it is still quite painful today. Different today than yesterday is the development of what feels like left shoulder bursitis.  We'll have to see how this goes over time.  There is extensive edema at the site, but not clear erythema [I'm dark skinned].  Still just can't seem to get enough water.  Had my first meal last night [made chicken soup].    It's still pretty early on. I'm not even at the 72 hour mark yet, so hopefully things will settle down over the next weeks.  I checked the box as life threatening because that was likely early anaphylaxis -- though at first I seriously thought at first I was just anxious because of the lip tingling.  This is in defense of the fact I did not self administer epi when I became SOB.  I likely should have, but know myself well and did fine without it and with asthma and allergy care. I didn't need extra albuterol after the first 24 hours [though writing this makes me feel SOB just from reliving it].   This second dose is a doozy.  Hope this was helpful. I provided you guys with my cell but if you want to follow up, I use my phone for work so if you text first I cant tell you availability.
OTHER_MEDS: cetirizine, monteleukast, gabapentin, duloxetine, baclofen, pr
HISTORY: arachnoiditis, controlled asthma, seasonal allergies, high cholesterol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: o Complaint The patient is a 41 year(s) old Female complaining of allergic reaction, nausea. o Chief Complaint Quote Patient complained of allergic reaction that started about 45 mins ago. She got her 1st dose of Pfizer Covid vaccine yesterday morning. She complained of rash all over the body, swelling on the hands and face including eyes and lips. She denied chest pain, abdominal pain, fever, cough, vomiting and difficulty breathing. She complained of nausea that started 5 mins ago. She has not taken any meds yet for her symptoms. o Time Seen 02-18-2021 01:20 o Historian patient  ADDITIONAL HPI: o Additional HPI Pt here with concerns of allergic reaction.  Pt fell asleep on the couch approx 2200.  She awoke 2 hours later with itching of her hands.  Over the next hour she developed a full body rash, itching, and swelling of face.  No wheezing, no difficulty swallowing.  Upon arrival to ED pt started to feel nauseated. Pt had first dose of COVID vaccine approx 16 hours prior to onset of sxs.   No h/o allergic reactions, no h/o asthma.  Emergency Department Course and Clinical Decision Making:   Patient presents with urticaria and swelling to her face eyes and lips.  Shortly upon being roomed she started to feel very nauseated and started vomiting.  No stridor or wheezing, no immediate airway compromise but given both cutaneous and GI symptoms, significant concern for anaphylaxis.  Patient was immediately given epinephrine intramuscularly, 0.3 mg.  An IV was placed and she was given Solu-Medrol, Benadryl, Pepcid, and Zofran.  Patient's urticaria and swelling started to nearly immediately improved after the epinephrine.  She is feeling much better though slightly anxious. To be reaction from the Pfizer vaccine, no other obvious triggers, patient has no history of allergic reactions or other sensitivities. We will observe in the emergency department in a monitored setting for several hours to assure no rebound symptoms, patient updated on plan.  0500 Pt has been resting.  Urticaria resolved, swelling to face resolved.  Discussed with pt reporting reaction to CDC, info provided. Also discussed the second dose of vaccine, recommended reaching out to Epi response team or PCP to get recommendations.  Will give short course of prednisone, 4 days, Benadryl as needed, ED return precautions discussed, will dc home.
Patient received second dose of Pfizer vaccine on 02/26/21. Starting having a fever from 02/27 and shortness of breath from 02/28.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 12-14 hours from receiving the 1st dose of the vaccine, I began to have symptoms that initially started as general malaise, fatigue, and muscle and aches and pains. By 2am On 2/09/21, I began having chills and by 6am, I had a fever of 101. F. Pain at the injection site started to develop , which I understood is a normal side effect of vaccines in general, but then over the course of hours to days, the pain began to radiate up my arm to my shoulder, and up my neck, to my head where a severe headache would ensue and render me unable to perform my daily activities. For days I was feeling unwell causing me to call out sick from my job as a nurse more than once. I also feel pain in my axilla and breast tissue adjacent to my arm pit, directly beneath the injection site. I also experienced nausea when the headache and muscle aches were at their worst. The fever eventually subsided after a few days, but the headache has persisted despite taking Ibuprofen as directed by my physician via a telehealth visit on day 3. (I called for an appointment on day 2, but they only had the next day available.) The headache pain is heavy, sharp, piercing, and throbbing, definitely interrupting with my daily activities. I have to go lay down and apply an ice pack to my head and neck area several times a day. These symptoms had been persisting for several days in a row and after being seen by my doctor again on the 8th day because of the symptoms, she recommended I go to the emergency room to address the persisting headaches and rule out any head bleeding and report the symptoms related to the vaccine. I was also advised by my physician to consider skipping the 2nd dose of the vaccine because of my severe reaction to the first one.
LAB_DATA: Cat Scan of the head performed in the Emergency Room

Patient received his first Moderna covid vaccine shot at about 4:00pm on 3/7/2021 and procedd to the post-vaccination observation area for his 15 minute observation period. About 10 minutes after his shot, patient alerted the an observation staff member that he was starting to feel hot. Staff member alert the pharmacist who had given him his shot and the pharmacist came over. Patient told the pharmacist he feels like he is burning up. Pharmacist took hi temperature an it in the 98 rang (can't remember the exact temp but was 98. something) Patient then then told the pharmacist that he feels like he is getting an aura of a coming seizure. The pharmacist applied an intant ice pack to the back of the patient neck and provided a bottle of cold water. Pharmacist stayed next to him talking to him and asking how he was doing and kept a hand on him in case he had a full blown seizure. Patient was awake but looked pale and seemed like he was going to fainted. Stayed like that for about 10 minutes. after about 10 minutes patient "came back". He looked back to normal and felt fine. During the process he called his wife to come get him and he was fine when she aroungs a few minutes later. Patient, wife, and pharmacist chatted for about 15 minutes before wife took him home. Patient said based on his history that it was a petit mal seizure.

The patient also started to feel very tired. The rash she had was similar but not as bad and the rash was more like red dots not full blisters but it was very itchy. On 12 Feb 2021, unspecified days prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number:007M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 12 Feb 2021, post receiving mRNA-1273, the patient had no reaction and did not feel bad.  On unspecified day in Feb 2021 one week prior to the reporting the events, the patient experienced chest pain and arm pain, minimum that lasted for 10 minutes. 3 or 4 night prior reporting the event, the patient was feeling abnormal, went to ER and was hospitalized with severe chest pain. The patient was in a regular room and was transferred to ICU. Next day, Cardiac catheterization was performed to see the patient's heart and found that 3 arteries in the original surgery were failing.  Treatment for the event, severe chest pain included morphine.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The event of arm pain was considered Recovered/Resolved. I called my physician on the morning of March 5th to notify him that I believed I was developing Shingles. I still had not developed the classic shingles rash but was now experiencing a headach, itchiness on the left side of my back,  fatigue,  a general achy feeling, pain that radiates from the left side of my spine through my rib cage and skin sensitivity to touch on my left abdomen at the level of my waistband that wraps around my left torso and through out the left side of my torso on my back.  He stated that it sounded line Shingles and started me on Famciclovir 500mg tablet 3 times a day for 10 days.  I have completed 4 days of the Famciclovir. My symptoms are about the same and I still have not developed the classic shingles rash.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 3:30 am. awoke crying which has never happen. Low feeling of depression lasted for 49 hours. Felt like a totally different human being. At that time, also experienced suicidal thoughts.

I received the vaccine at 4:30 PM and later that night, I had a headache and I felt very out of it. By the end of the day; however, I was feeling better. The next day, I woke up around 5 AM and my muscles were all tensing very strongly and I could not stop shaking. This went on for about 30 minutes, and then I stopped shaking and tensing  so much, though my muscles still felt a bit tense. I can't really eat in the morning, so I drank two glasses of water over the course of a few hours and took 2 acetaminophen. I stayed in bed until around 10 AM. Then, I took a shower, but while taking it, I felt very lightheaded and my vision had some black spots, and I had to sit down several times. After I got out, I tried to eat something, but then I felt really nauseous and had acid reflux for at least 30 minutes. Afterwards, I drank a bit of water and went back to bed. My muscles started tensing and shaking again, though not quite as intensely as when I first woke up. I felt very cold, so I turned up the heat and put on warm clothes. I fell asleep for about 20 minutes around 12, and when I woke up I felt a little less nauseous and headache-y. I stayed in bed for an hour, and I ate some pudding over the course of an hour or two, but I thinking about eating much else made me feel nauseous. I fell asleep around 5:30 and woke up again around 7:30. I felt better after waking up, but still had a bit of a headache and my muscles were slightly tense. On Sunday and Monday (today) I felt about the same, physically tired but otherwise mostly ok.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My second COVID-19 vaccination injection on Friday morning, 2/19/2021 resulted initially (starting on Saturday, the day following the vaccination} in a sore right wrist and a much more painful right arm that steadily grew in intensity and spread rather rapidly into my upper torso.  By the following day (Sunday, 2/21) my breasts became very sensitive and I had severe pains across my back.  This may or may not have been the beginning of a banding type MS exacerbation, but by Monday, 2/22, it was clear that I was experiencing a full-blown and seriously disabling exacerbation. Both legs experienced the tingling and numbness I have had in a prior exacerbation, and by the time I was able to talk to Dr. (my neurologist) on Monday afternoon (2/22), the numbness had progressed upward into my lower abdomen and I was no longer able to stand at all.  It appears highly likely that the MS attack was triggered by the response of my immune system's reacting to the discomfort and severe body pains that occurred following the vaccination.  I told Dr. of the total loss of feeling and use of both legs and was experiencing a increasing numbness from toes up to abdomen.  Before ordering the high doses of corticosteroids used to stop my exacerbation, Dr. sent me to the Emergency Room for testing to make sure I did not have an infection that could be covered up by the steroids.  When this testing did not show any such infection, the ER administered an IV infusion of 1 gram of solumedrol, followed by gradually decreasing high oral doses of prednisone.  As of this date, numbness has started decreasing and some limited  utility of right leg has returned.  Still i can no longer stand and perform even the minimal movements to-and-from wheelchair to bed or toilet without substantial physical help (not needed before this exacerbation) from my sole caregiver, my husband.
LAB_DATA: Emergency room tests indicated only the presence of a continuing chronic urinary tract infection, which I have had for many years and nothing else

I was awaken at approx 5:00am the morning  following my 2nd Moderna Covid 19 vaccine with my upper left arm severly aching.  The person who gave me the shot informed that if my arm hurt I could use a cold pack and take aspirin, which I did that morning.  Approx 30 minutes after applying the cold pack, I became extremely cold and my entire body shivering.  I wrapped up in a blanket and drifted in and out of sleep for about 5-6 hours, cold and shivering the entire time.  When getting up to get water or use the restroom, my arms and legs were extremely weak and wobbly.  I almost felt as if my legs would collapse under me when walking.  I took my temperature throughout and it was at a normal level.  Around 11:00am, the cold and shivering subsided but then I began to feel warm.  I continued to take my temperature and it was continually climbing until it reached 103.2 degrees before beginning to reduce down.  My weakness and wobbleness also continued and I had a severe headache. I also vomited 1 time.   At approx 7:00pm, my temperature was back to normal and I began feeling a lot better.  I have had no further symptoms since then.

I took 800mg of ibuprofen and 100 mg of Benadryl before calling 911.  I went to sleep after EMS left.  I continued to feel achy and sick until the following Tuesday. My mother has experienced a severe reaction to her vaccine. Diagnosed with brain encephalopathy probably caused by molecular mimicry in response to the Covid vaccine, she is now being treated as an inpatient at the Clinic.  She was fully independent- living alone, mobile, with excellent cognitive function.  On January 21, 2021 she received her 1st Moderna vaccine. Subsequently family noticed small balance changes, slight fine motor coordination changes (handwriting, etc) and a little forgetfulness not previously seen. Everything was chalked up to her being 89 years old.  She remained independent and relatively fully functional.  Patient is now unable to stand without assistance, leans backward when trying to stand, has developed a spastic tremor bilaterally in her arms, and her cognition is completely altered.  Hallucinations, memory loss, can follow some directions but not all, speech clear but inappropriate.  This declines DAILY. As of March 7th, she could not identify immediate family members in a photo. These changes have all occurred within the past few weeks and appear to have an acute underlying cause not related to age.    Medical staff are looking at an autoimmune encephalitis picture based on the antibodies developed from the vaccine attacking the tissue in the brain and spinal cord that resembles the small piece of the vaccine.    She is currently at the Clinic affiliated hospital. At this time, family is contacting Clinic main campus to request further investigation.   Photographic evidence of rapid decline available, but not able to attach to this form:   Available are three pictures of a log patient keeps with her vitals that she was doing every day.  1. Personal log of vital signs� pre Covid vaccine/dose 1 - you can see the handwriting is concise, clear, and orderly.   2. Personal log of vitals after Covid dose 1 on Jan. 21 - slight changes in the handwriting and orderliness but still ok.  3. Personal log of vitals after Covid vaccine dose 2 � Feb. 17 - note the illegible handwriting, missing entries, and no spatial awareness of line alignment.  Available are three photos of crossword puzzles she does every day.    1. Puzzle dated Feb.12. Demonstrates her ability to accurately fill most answers with clear writing.   2. Puzzle dated Feb.19 shows an ability to fill in only a couple answers with obvious handwriting changes.   3. Puzzle dated Feb. 21 shows inability to complete, and a strange discrepancy between ability and inability- note 29 across and 18 down.  Patients outcome is undetermined as diagnosis/treatment and prognosis are ongoing.

Had a fever for 2-3 days.; This spontaneous report was received from a consumer via other's company letter, and refers to an 88-year-old male patient. On an unknown date in 2015, the patient was vaccinated with Pneumococcal Vaccine, Polyvalent (23-valent) (manufacturer unknown) as prophylaxis (formulation, dose, dose number, route of administration, anatomical site of vaccination, lot number, and expiration date were not provided). Additionally, the patient stated he experienced a bad reaction to it, he had fever (Pyrexia) for 2-3 days.  On an unspecified day in September 2020, the patient had a blood transfusion. Also, he stated his hemoglobin had not quite gotten to where it needed to be. It was 4 pints, but may be measured differently at the hospital. Every other time, the patient underwent to a drawing of his blood to check on his hemoglobin (also reported "Reason for drawing blood was to check on his very low hemoglobin") (haemoglobin decreased). He clarified it "was a matter of routine". Additionally, the reporter stated a doctor wanted to be preventative from getting the disease. He had a weak, old man voice and sounded like if there was a frog in his voice all of the time. Voice was not as clear as it used to be (dysphonia).  On 20-JAN-2021, the patient had a blood drawn (unknown results).     On 21-JAN-2021, the patient was vaccinated with the first shot of sars-cov-2 spike protein mrna vaccine (PFIZER) (lot number EL3247 and expiration date 01-MAR-2021), administered in the left shoulder as prophylaxis of COVID-19.  On 03-FEB-2021, the patient had another blood drawn where his liver enzymes shot up over 400 points (hepatic enzyme increased).         At the time of reporting, the outcome of haemoglobin decreased and dysphonia was reported as not recovered/not resolved. The outcome of hepatic enzyme increased was unknown. an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body; flu like symptoms; high blood pressure; insomnia; increase pulse; Dilated pupils; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 39-year-old, female patient who received Modern's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced flu like symptoms, a feeling of an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body/tremor, high blood pressure/increased blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupil/mydriasis and increase pulse/heart rate increased.  The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.    On 24-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received the second dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown)on left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 25-Jan-2021, The patient experienced flu like symptoms, but in the afternoon of the same day she also started to experience an internal "vibrating" tremor inside of her body.  She had this symptom for 4 weeks now along with high blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupils and increase pulse. A neurologist told her that it could be an adrenergic hyper response to the vaccine.  No Laboratory details provided.  Treatment information provided was beta blockers prescribed in the ER visit.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events is not applicable.   At the time of this report, the outcome of the events experienced flu like symptoms, a feeling of an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body, high blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupil and increase pulse is Unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 39 Y/O F with a serious unexpected event of tremor and NS unexpected influenza like illness, blood pressure increased, heart rate increased, mydriasis, insomnia, and possibly a "adrenergic hyper response to the vaccine". Treated with beta blockers. Event onset 2 days after first dose mRNA-1273. Outcome unknown. SYMPTOM_TEXT: A 17 year old received a COVID-19 vaccination.  The patient proceeded through the normal vaccination process on 9 February 2021.  The vaccination team failed to identify him as medically ineligible due to age.  He had no complications.  The error was not discovered until he presented for his second dose on 9 March 2021.   The positive identification process requires ID card verification, which is documented with a scanner that feeds an excel spreadsheet.  This process is also used to verify the patient is in the appropriate vaccination tier.  The scan and spreadsheet were accomplished correctly, and the patient was verified as an employee in the appropriate tier.  The staff at the table failed to note the age of the patient. The medical screening process requires the staff to check the ID card and the DHA Form 207.  The DHA Form 207 was completed correctly.  Staff failed to note the age of the patient.  The vaccinator reviews the DHA Form 207 for completeness prior to the time-out and vaccination.  This step does not require documentation.  If this step was completed, staff failed to note the age of the patient.

Around 8:30p.m. Saturday  March 6, 2021 I began to feel chills. I laid down around 9:30p.m to go to sleep. I woke up at 12:25a.m (Sunday March 7th, 2021) with a fever of 104.3 and was experiencing extreme neck and head pain. My hands hurt as if I had arthritis and couldn't make them feel better. I was very short of breath and dry coughing. I took Tylenol and tried to lay back down and was able to go back to sleep around 3:00a.m. I got up at 6:10am and my temp was 101.6. I took Ibuprofen at this point and by 9:30am my temp was 99.8. I was still experiencing a very bad headache and my neck and back were achy. I felt a lot better by about 11:00am, took a hot shower and laid down for a nap around 2:00pm Sunday. When I woke up around 3:15p.m I had spiked yet another fever of 102.0 and was having bad body aches again in my neck and head area and it continued to get worse though my back over the next hour. I was experiencing a dry cough again also but this time it was more constant. It took over 3 hours for my fever to go below 100.0 with alternating Tylenol and Ibuprofen. It finally broke around 7:00p.m. I had a lot of pain in my neck and head the rest of the night. I woke up Monday March 8th, 2021 with a moderate headache but it went away throughout the day. No fever returned Monday. The only time I experienced coughing and shortness of breath was while I had the fever.
OTHER_MEDS: YAZ Birth Control, Vitamin B Complex, Vitamin C, Vitamin D, Loratadine (OTC)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: throat seized up twice/ throat tightening; Initial information was received on 28-Jan-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received from a patient (consumer or non-healthcare professional) via global medical information (reference number- 00450721) and transmitted to Sanofi on 28-Jan-2021.  This case involves a 65-year-old female patient who experienced throat seized up twice, throat tightening (throat tightness), after she received FLUZONE.  Medical history, medical treatment and family history were not provided.  It was reported that, as past vaccination the patient received flu vaccines annually for many years and on 14-Dec-2006, patient was vaccinated with FLUZONE. List concomitant or no other vaccines was not asked at the time of reporting.   On 13-Dec-2007, the patient received a 0.5 mL dose of suspect INFLUENZA VACCINE (produced by unknown manufacturer) [lot number, expiry date and other dosing details were not reported] for prophylactic vaccination.  On the same day, on the way on her way home after receiving the vaccine, patient experienced throat tightening.   It was reported that, her throat seized up twice, she could breathe, but her throat felt as if it was clamping shut. It was abrupt and sudden. Then her throat abruptly unclamped and she continued home. About 4 hours later at 21:00 her throat tightened again.  It was also reported that, patient checked with the pharmacy who checked their records and provided the national drug code (NDC) numbers from her vaccinations.  Health care professional stated that, it may be due to an ingredient, but patient was is not allergic to eggs also patient requests to know if she can take the corona virus disease (COVID) vaccine and wanted to know about throat tightening reactions to flu vaccine How could she find out the ingredients in the NDC's she was given.   Details of laboratory data were not reported.  It was not reported if the patient received any corrective treatment.  On an unknown date, patient had recovered from the events.  There will be no information available on batch number for this case.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Menactra was administered two days after the expiration date, with no reported adverse event; Initial information regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received from an other health professional via agency (Reference number- 00495741) and transmitted to Sanofi on 26-Feb-2021.  This case involves a 24 years old female patient who was vaccinated 0.5 ml second dose of MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE [MENACTRA], solution for injection (lot number- U6543AB, expiration date- 23-FEB-2021) via intramuscular route in the right deltoid for prophylactic vaccination on 25-FEB-2021 and reported that Menactra was administered two days after the expiration date (expired product administered).  The patient's past medical history, medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided.  No concomitant medications were given to the patient.  It was a case of actual medication error due to expired vaccine used (same day latency). Also reported that the caller would like to know how to proceed in caring for the patient. MIA (Manufacturing and/or importation activities) transferred Health Care Professional who asked for appropriate follow-up after expired Menactra was given.   It was not reported whether the patient had any adverse event.  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holder's compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.

This is a 60-year-old female who just received her second Pfizer dose of the Covid vaccine earlier today when she says she felt immediately a flushing of her left arm where she had received the vaccination and then some tingling and abruptly followed with difficulty swallowing tongue enlargement, and feeling like she had to "search for my air". This required her to turn her head leftward to assist in her breathing. She has no associated pruritus. She was given an intramuscular injection of epinephrine at the clinic where she received the vaccination and EMS was activated. She did not demonstrate any changes in her phonation or signs of stridor and there was no wheezing or signs of facial or oral swelling on arrival of paramedics. She received additional intramuscular injection of epinephrine and IV Benadryl and Solu-Medrol at that time followed by an albuterol inhalation treatment and transported here as a medical alert. She reports the symptoms are similar to what she is experienced with multiple bee sting allergic reactions in the past. She is never required intubation. She never develops any facial swelling or urticaria.
LAB_DATA: She is placed on cardiac monitor.  She maintains normal O2 saturations on room air.  She is given 0.5 mg of Ativan and soft tissue neck radiographs performed.  No signs of abnormal soft tissue swelling.  Patient is observed and after the Ativan reports significant subjective improvement.  Her vital signs returned to normal range.

I am not sure what stopped the shaking, but I had tried to put my body weight over my legs  (body folded in half) to try to stop the shaking and took 1 regular strength tylenol.  After the shaking ended, up until I went to sleep (maybe 3-4 hours later) I felt some numbness and tingling in my finger tips and feet.  The next day, I felt fine but emailed my Rheumatologist to report the shaking and she directed me to report it here.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Event as reported in employee's own words:  "I experienced LUQ abdominal pain,nausea, vomiting after the 1st dose of the Moderna vaccine which lasted for almost 2 weeks, mostly mild in intensity. I received my 2nd dose on Jan 23rd, by Tuesday Jan 26th I started having the above symptoms again with mild to moderate intensity of the abdominal pain. This persisted longer and I reached out to my primary care team to be checked for pancreatitis. I was advised by my primary care team to get seen at the ER which I did last Feb 9th. It did show my lipase level elevated which the ER providers said a "little bumped". US of my pancreas did not show it swollen/inflamed. I was discharged the same day. The LUQ pain improving but still there. "  ED Summary: "The patient is a 53-year-old woman with history of type 2 diabetes, medication induced pancreatitis 10 years ago who presents for abdominal pain.  Patient's pain is concerning for medication/vaccine induced pancreatitis versus cholelithiasis versus cholecystitis versus gastritis versus colitis versus peptic ulcer disease.  Pancreatitis most likely as labs obtained showed an elevated lipase (94 units/L) and normal liver function tests and bilirubin.  Patient has normal white blood cell count as well as hemoglobin and hematocrit.  Patient had normal blood glucose on arrival then was feeling slightly woozy at time of evaluation following her right upper quadrant ultrasound and had a blood glucose of 85 after being n.p.o. in the ED for approximately 3 hours.  Patient given crackers and juice with good response.  Right upper quadrant ultrasound showed no bile duct dilation, no gallstones, normal gallbladder, normal pancreas and stable known left renal cyst and known simple hepatic cyst." Patient discharged home on low-fat diet until symptoms resolve and PRN acetaminophen for pain.
PRIOR_VAX: abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting with first Moderne COVID vaccine.
ALLERGIES: Iodinated contrast - anaphylaxis, hives Nizatidine - undocumented reaction Seafood - anaphylaxis

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Got vaccine at 5:36 pm and during waiting time afterward, she reported around 5;53 pm having generalized tingling then followed by generalized pruritis. Denied and did not exhibit signs of urticaria, angioedema, cough, dyspnea, wheezing, CP, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, lightheadedness, weakness, pallor, tachycardia. Discussed giving her diphenhydramine and she agreed stating she had no previous adverse reaction to this treatment. At 5:56 pm, I gave diphenhydramine HCL 50 mg/ml 1 ml IM in her right deltoid muscle. Around the time of the injection (approximately 5:59 pm, pulse was 76, oxygen saturation 97%, BP 138/90, lungs clear, heart RRR. Within 20 minutes (6:22 pm) of diphenhydramine injection, she reported that the tingling had largely subsided (only remaining in lower legs) and her pruritis was improving. Her pulse was 77, oxygen saturation 96%, and BP 126/82 at that time. She also reported she had not developed any new symptoms (see above). By 6:28 pm, she reported no further tingling nor pruritis and feeling well. We released her at that time as we deemed her recovered from the symptoms. On or about 02-MAR-2018, the pt was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dose, strength, route, batch/lot# and expiration date were unknown) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). On unknown dates, after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt suffered multiple outbreaks of herpes zoster and postherpetic neuralgia. As a result of these symptoms, Plaintiff was seen and treated by medical providers and was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations not presented prior to using the product. The pt also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of the pt's condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the wrongful conduct, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of the company's conduct, the pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of post herpetic neuralgia and herpes zoster was considered as not recovered. The reporter considered herpes zoster and postherpetic neuralgia to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).   Herpes zoster and postherpetic neuralgia were considered as disabling.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 9 hours after vaccine, developed body aches and rigors, low grade temp to ~100.   Fatigued, so went to bed and took ibuprofen.  Continued to have significant body aches and rigors.  While lying in bed, developed nausea.  I got up to go to the bathroom and woke up on the bathroom floor after a syncopal episode.  I returned to bed bed and still felt very lightheaded and laid down.  I had another brief syncopal episode while lying down.  I felt short of breath and had chest tightness when I woke up.  This was around 11pm.  I was evaluated in the ED, where I continued to have body aches and rigors.  I developed fever to 101 and was given Advil and Tylenol as well as IVF.  Symptoms finally resolved.  Had COVID test (which was negative), CBC, chemistries, EKG, chest x-ray, all of which were negative/normal.  Continued to feel significantly fatigued for an additional 48 hours.
LAB_DATA: 1/14/21: Chest x-ray - normal EKG - wnl COVID PCR NP swab - negative CBC - wnl LFT's - wnl chemistries - wnl Urine HCG - wnl Urinalysis - wnl

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient and husband arrived to received covid-19 vaccine together, 12:30 pm and 12:45 pm appointments. I informed patients that if they wanted to, they can both enter room together. Both patients were counseled on side effects/ what to expect. Patient was administered the Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine first in left arm. Upon vaccination, patient's arm began to bleed from injection site. I informed patient I would clean her arm, and attempted to hold gauze in place myself. Patient stated she would hold the gauze instead. After applying bandaid and cleaning area, I began process to vaccinate her husband. While vaccinating husband, patient stated she felt dizzy/faint. Patient sat in chair. Husband stated she is prone to fainting spells. I offered EMS services.Husband refused. I elevated patient's legs with other chair. Patient started to become non-responsive.  I stated I would use an epi-pen. Patient's husband refused epipen. Informed technician, to contact 911. Informed technician to contact front end manager. Patient continued to be non-responsive. Asked husband if I should get patient juice. Ran to get patient orange juice and straw. Husband wet patient with water. Patient started drinking orange juice through straw. Felt better. Started becoming responsive. PAtient and husband waited for EMS. Refused EMS services.

Thirty hours in, I had joint aches in my spine (mainly neck and low back); low grade fever; nauseated;  headache. I felt like everything was it  was swollen  and tight - I couldn't wear my watch on my wrist. Almost like lymph system - nothing tight in my arm pits; felt like my pants were too tight in my groin - my body was swollen by my lymph nodes. Developed all kinds of gas in my stomach.  I was having chest pains - 3 or 4 times a month before the vaccine - after the vaccine - I'm having the chest pains daily. That lasted for about 12 hours. Next day, 22nd, I developed diarrhea for 24 hours.  9 days later - I got numbness and tingling started radiating down my wrist into my fingers; lower calf to my feet and I had to go see my orthopedic surgeon - it was radiating down into my feet. He sent me to a podiatrist and he doesn't know.  Those symptoms still haven't resolved. When I wake up - it's a low level and by night time my feet would get so numb and tingly it drove me crazy and then it went into my hands. Went to my doctor on March 2nd - my doctor thought I was having a histamine response in my body. I took an antihistamine - and half my symptoms went away. My esophagus is going into spasms -  and I am trying to see a GI specialist. I was taking Benadryl last week but I got too tired. So I take 2 Benadryl at night now and I'm taking a Zyrtec (generic) at the day - it takes the edge off but doesn't resolve the symptoms entirely. Eleven day - I developed a floaty in my right eye - a black spot. I went to my eye doctor - it looks like my eye is healthy -but floaty is not going away. So talking on the phone, My throat is starting to swell up and feels like something back there and the more I talk pretty soon I start losing my voice (happening now on the phone). They added to my meds: Pepsid, Viscus lidocaine;  Mylanta after every meal; Pantoprazole;  Sucralfate; gave me another one but I haven't taken it yet: Hyoscyamine - for really bad spasms and I haven't had another really bad one since I went to ER (besides taking the antihistamines).  I have seen 5 specialists all together.

Additional details were provided as follows: The patient received Shingrix and had itchy rash on her left arm near injection site that appeared the night of the injection. The health care provider gave her a CAT (computerized tomogram) scan that was negative. SYMPTOM_TEXT: At approx 2 pm Monday, March 8, 2021 I was shopping for clothes.  I was having difficulty breathing through my mask and asked employee if they had a mask I can have.  When I took mine off to use theirs, I was surprised it wasn't my usual KN95 on me as those are more difficult to breath through.  I felt labored in breathing from that point.  I left the store to get home quickly.  I was also experiencing rapid heart rate\great nervousness and was assuming that because I purchased a large diet coke one hr before that, that the caffeine was causing this.  However, I've never experienced this event.  Within 3 minutes of my home, I started experiencing what seemed to be shortness of breathe.  it lasted about a minute.  I considered going to ER.  But went home.  Shortness of breathe stopped and I looked on google how to reduce caffeine reaction.  I ate handful of peanuts for protein, but had odd indigestion.  Kept drinking lots of water to flush out.  Was doing many deep breathing exercises. Nervousness and rapid heart rate lasted about 2 hours.  I  was back to normal by evening.  Scary as I never experienced difficulty with a regular surgical mask.  Never experienced such a severe reaction to a caffeine beverage.  Never experienced that shortness of breath.
OTHER_MEDS: Hydrochlorothiazide 12.5 mg am daily Meloxicam 15 mg  restarted Sunday pm,  March 7, 2021  Acetaminophen 500 mg (2) Monday 11:30 am, March 8, 2021

Co-suspect products included COVID-19 VACCINE (COVID 19 VACCINE) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included bursitis (had bursitis about one year ago and about 10 to 11 years before that).   On 28th December 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular) .5 ml. On an unknown date, the dose was an unknown dose. On an unknown date, the patient received COVID 19 VACCINE. In December 2020, less than a week after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced injected limb mobility decreased, shoulder pain, pain in arm, radiating pain, bursitis, axillary pain and activities of daily living impaired. On an unknown date, the patient experienced injection site discoloration. The patient was treated with paracetamol (Tylenol). Additional details were provided as follows: The reporter reported for herself. The patient received dose of Shingrix in the left deltoid. The patient received covid 19 vaccine in the right arm. The reporter stated that, a day or two after the Shingrix shot, the patient experiencing shoulder pain in the left shoulder similar to bursitis. The patient stated that, the pain had been in different areas of the shoulder and had made it difficult for her to put on her car seatbelt. It had also affected her mobility with respect to dressing herself (putting on pajamas) and it was painful to wear an apron because she could no longer reach behind her back to tie the apron herself. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I want to preface this by saying that I believe the vaccine was administered more posterior and superior than a IM injection into the deltoid should be. This was confirmed by other health providers. Approximately 1 week s/p vaccine dose 1, I was lifting weights around 8PM (bench press), when I noticed some sudden soreness/pain in my shoulder joint on my left side (5/10). I returned home and around 11PM my shoulder felt mildly pruritic and very warm to the touch. I noticed a nodule palpable under the skin, measuring approximately 1cm, and it was then that I realized that it was in the same location of my vaccination injection (I will include photos of injection site and reaction). The nodule continued to grow ~2cm, when I decided to call the advice nurse line, (I am a 2nd yr MD-PhD student). I was advised to take diphenhydramine and go to the ER if I felt anaphylactic reaction occurring, and they made me a morning appt with the NP at the clinic. The diphenhydramine seemed to stop the progression, however the following morning the 2cm nodule was still present and warm to the touch, but was no longer pruritic. The NP received photos and advised that I continue antihistamines - diphenhydramine at night and loratidine during the day for ~5 days. She did agree that the injection was not a proper deltoid injection. Over the course of 3 days the nodule disappeared. I had no issues with the second vaccination.
LAB_DATA: Will include photos via email with this report. No labs or tests were performed.
HISTORY: Cervical hyperplasia s/p LEEP - resolved,  exercise induced asthma (dx 03/2020 -- rx'ed inhaler but do not use unless exercising outdoors in spring -- have not used in 1 year), actinic keratosis s/p excision - resolved.
ALLERGIES: Never had allergies to any medications or food products. Have seasonal allergies -- tested and allergic to tree pollen and most specifically oak trees.

The patient's medical history included high blood pressure, and thyroid disorder.  Concomitant medications included enalapril hydrochlorothiazide, simvastatin for "cholesterol" and a "thyroid medication."  On 29-Jan-2021, at 0931, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 004M20A ) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 29-Jan-2021, 46 minutes after vaccine administration, patient reported that she started feeling like a heavy weight was pressuring her chest from the inside and also felt like a heavy pressure was coming from outside her body. At 1100, she stated that she experienced a feeling like a heavy thing was moving across her chest and she reportedly had a hard time breathing. Her oxygen level dropped to 80%, but by breathing intensely she managed to bring it to 84-87%. She reported her pulse to be 115. All of these symptoms lasted for 20 minutes. Later, she reported that her oxygen level returned to 90% and then eventually to 94%.  However, she reported that for the next few days she felt like her heart rate was fast through the day, for about 5 days.  She said that she felt like it was beating really fast and felt like it was moving up her throat, giving her a choking feeling. Since last Friday, 05-Feb-2021, she stated that she has had no more problems. Patient reached out to her HCP who denied her any post-vaccine related attention.    Treatment activities for event included taking ibuprofen 600 mg after the vaccination.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Patient presented to medical center emergency room on 02/21/2020 at 19:00, patient complained of shortness of breath and feeling fullness of her throat. Patient stated that she had Motrin 800 mg TID and Flexeril PRN due to her back pain. Patient also stated that she ate a banana after she took her medications. Her systolic blood pressure was 50, and her HR was 109, patient also stated that she had her 2 shots of Moderna Vaccine, her first shot was on 01/06 and her second shot was on 02/02. Patient was treated with:  1 Duoneb, 0.3 ML IM of epinephrine, Solumedrol 125 mg, Benadryl IV 50 mg, Normal Saline infusion IV 1000 ml/hr, and Pepcid IV 20 mg.  Patient lactic acid was 10.6, WBC 24.2 and Temp 97 F, patient was diagnosed as sepsis shock and patient received:  Piperacillin-tazobactam 3.375 g in D5W 50 ml IVPB (3.375 g once)  Vancomycin 1 g in D5W 200 ml IVPB (1 g once).  Patient pH was < 6.780 and PCO2 was 55 and bicarbonate level was 5.0, patient received Sodium bicarbonate IV 50 mEq once.  Patient was not stable as her BP and HR were fluctuating patient received DilTlazem IV 2.5 mg for 2 doses. Patient received Levophed 16 mg /NS 250 ml IV.  At 23:13 patient was intubated, patient received a local anesthesia through a central line of lidocaine 2% without epinephrine, and patient was transferred to the ICU to be monitored. At 00:33 CODE BLUE was called and patient became unresponsive and lost pulse while patient was brought to ICU. Patient was coded twice before ROSC, during intubation patient patient noted to have coffee-ground drainage.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2 days after my 1st vaccine (Thursday, 3/4), I started to feel a slight shortness of breath...it was not severe but felt pretty constant regardless if I was still or moving...not a full catching of breath but the sensation was there  I went to Urgent Care on Friday 3/5 to get tested for COVID, and that came back negative on Rapid (3/5) and PCR (3/7)  The symptom continued into Monday 3/8, and I went back to Urgent Care to get a Chest X-Ray and Blood work.  The Chest X Ray came back normal, but the D Dimer showed an elevated level and they recommended I go get a CT Scan to check for Blood Clots  I went to NY Presbyterian ER to get a CT Scan with Contrast, which came back clean.  They also did a ECG 12 Lead and Troponin I Test, all came back clean  I was discharged on 3/8, with Hospital potentially diagnosing the issue as Pluerisy.  This could be from a common cold, but also concerned that the vax caused some internal inflammation   Still feeling the sensation on 3/9, have a follow up appointment with GP on Friday 3/12 to go over all tests

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 15-minutes of vaccination, the patient reported a diffuse pruritic rash with hives, dizziness, blurred vision, and SOB. EMS evaluated the patient on-site. Patient was hypertensive (173/92). EMS administered 50mg Benadryl IV and 2L Oxygen via nasal canula. Given past medical history of allergic reactions, EMS transported the patient to  Hospital Emergency Department. In the ED, the patient remained hypertensive. EKG demonstrated NSR, rate 75bom, no ST-T changes, no ectopy, and normal PR & QRS intervals. Blood work was unremarkable. After administration of Benadryl the patient noted improvement of their hives and was discharged with a diagnosis of allergic reaction secondary to COVID vaccine that caused acute hives.
